課程大綱-學士







Your browser does not support JavaScript!
Your browser does not support JavaScript!





拓樸學-學























科目資料 
<[中文科目名稱]> 拓樸學  
<[英文科目名稱]> Topology  
<[科目代碼]> AM__31500  
<[班別]> 學士班  
<[修別]> 選修  
<[學分數]> 3  
<[時數]> 3  
<[一、課程目標]> 從H. Poincare於20世紀初開創近世拓樸學的研究後，拓樸學已發展成上一世紀 最重要的數學之一。幾何學，分析學和其相關的學門，也借重拓樸來描述。因此 ，教授拓樸學使學生能有基本的瞭解。進而使學生有學習研究高深數學的基礎。  
<[二、資源需求評估]> 本系專兼任教師  
<[三、先修課程]> 無  
<[四、課程綱要]> (I)Preliminaries: Sets and Functions. (II)Metric Spaces: Definitions and Examples, Open and Closed sets, Convergence, Completeness, Baire’s Theorem, Continuous Mappings, Space of Continuous Functions and Euclidean and Unitary Spaces. (III) Topological Spaces: Definitions and Examples, Elementary Concepts, Open Bases and Open Subbases, Weak Topology and Function Algebras. (IV) Compactness: Compact Spaces, Products of Spaces, Tychonoff’s Theorem, Locally Compact spaces, Compactness of Metric Spaces and Ascoli’s Theorem. (V) Separation: T_1 Spaces and Hausdorff Spaces, Completely Regular Spaces and Normal Spaces, Urysohn’s Lemma and the Tietze Extension Theorem, The Urysohn Imbedding Theorem and the Stone-Cech Compactification. (VI) Connectedness: Connected Spaces, The Components of a Space, Totally Disconnected Spaces and Locally Connected Spaces. (VII) Approximation: The Weierstrass Approximation Theorem, The Stone-Weierstrass Theorem, Locally Compact Hausdorff Spaces and The Extended Stone-Weierstrass Theorem.  
<[五、教學要求進行方式之建議]> 教學方式主要是以課堂講授，學生演習和測驗為主  
<[六、適用入學新生年度]>






















瀏覽數  





























Department of Applied Mathematics, A330 Science and Engineering Building I, National Dong Hwa University, Hualien, Taiwan 97401 TEL: +886-3-863-3513, 863-3514, 863-3561; FAX:+886-3-863-3510; Email:math@gms.ndhu.edu.tw








